im not just one of the greatest Filipino athletes but also one of the most decorated gymnasts in history.  And it took Yulo to hit one of thelowest pointsof his career as his storied Olympic campaign came just less than a year since he went home empty-handed from the previous World Artistic Gymnastics Championships.  But Yulo kept the faith in himself and delivered on the biggest stage in sports.  He\\u00a0nailed his opening Ri Se Gwang vault - a front handspring double piked salto with a half twist - to earn 15.433 points, the highest by a male gymnast in the apparatus in this Olympics.  Yulo then landed a Kasamatsu double twist that gave him 14.800 points and an average of 15.116 points on the way to becoming the first Filipino to win multiple medals in a single Olympics.  Agem from the grassrootswho got discovered in the Palarong Pambansa, Yulo joined an exclusive club of multiple Olympic medalists from the Philippines that includes swimmer Teofilo Yldefonso and weightlifter Hidilyn Diaz.  Yldefonso won a bronze each in the 1928 Amsterdam and 1932 Los Angeles Games, while Diaz captured the Philippines'breakthrough goldin Tokyo after she copped silver in the 2016 Rio de Janeiro Olympics.  Three years since Diaz ended the golden drought, Yulo produced two more as the Philippines - celebrating its100th yearof Olympic participation - takes home multiple golds from a single Games for the first time.  With two golds from Yulo, the Philippines has matched itsfour-medal haulin Tokyo - its biggest in Olympic history - as boxersNesthy PetecioandAira Villegasare assured of at least a bronze.- Rappler.com  How does this make you feel?  follow us          \"}"